Package: arkhaia
Title: Archaeological and Historical Analysis
Version: 0.5.5
Date: 2026-04-11
Authors@R: 
    person(c("Stephen", "A."), "Collins-Elliott", , "sce@utk.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5642-6903"))
Description: Tools for quantitative analysis related to archaeological and historical problems for irreguarly-spaced time indexed observations, toward evaluating temporal patterns of changing similarity among past contexts. Data may either be occurence of event over time as a temporal point process (TPP), e.g., deposition or use event of an artifact, measurements, e.g., prices, or count data. Methods include least squares spectral analysis by lowest frequency iteration (LSSA-LFI) for model fitting, Anderson-Cramer-von Mises distance for TPP, threshold detection for TPP, bias-corrected Cramer's V for homogeneity, and simulation from a truncated Poisson distribution for random right-censoring of count data.
